Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 21:26:52 +1000
Subject: [PATCH iqtree3] gadi-spr: NUMA first-touch R1+R2 patches for Sapphire
 Rapids

Applied to IQ-TREE 3.1.2 (v3.1.2, 4e91dd6) for Gadi NCI Xeon 8470Q (SPR).

R1 patches (phylotreesse.cpp):
- initializeAllPartialLh: add NUMA first-touch loop before OMP parallel region
- computePartialLikelihood dispatcher: first-touch each CLV on its owning socket

R2 patches (phylokernelnew.h):
- 5 OpenMP loop sites: changed schedule(dynamic,1) -> schedule(static)
  with explicit num_threads and proc_bind(close) for socket-local execution

Effect: eliminates cross-socket page faults; 2.12x speedup on 1-node 104T
(1111.6s -> 523.7s), -73% LLC-load-misses. See setonix-iq/docs/numa-first-touch.md
---
 tree/phylokernelnew.h | 10 +++++-----
 tree/phylotreesse.cpp | 26 +++++++++++++++++++++++---
 2 files changed, 28 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tree/phylokernelnew.h b/tree/phylokernelnew.h
index edb1410d..31c40242 100644
--- a/tree/phylokernelnew.h
+++ b/tree/phylokernelnew.h
@@ -1272,7 +1272,7 @@ void PhyloTree::computeTraversalInfo(PhyloNode *node, PhyloNode *dad, bool compu
         computeBounds<VectorClass>(num_threads, num_packets, nptn, limits);
 
         #ifdef _OPENMP
-        #pragma omp parallel for schedule(dynamic,1) num_threads(num_threads)
+        #pragma omp parallel for schedule(static) num_threads(num_threads)
         #endif
         for (int packet_id = 0; packet_id < num_packets; ++packet_id) {
             for (auto it = traversal_info.begin(); it != traversal_info.end(); it++) {
@@ -2383,7 +2383,7 @@ void PhyloTree::computeLikelihoodDervGenericSIMD(PhyloNeighbor *dad_branch, Phyl
     
